# Public Materials Alignment

When editing matched files, keep cross-channel consistency.

## Required consistency
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Headline focus | Operations Analyst · logistics / supply chain / SQL |
| GPA | **3.43** only |
| Graduation | Class of 2027 |
| Degree abbreviation | **B.S.** only (Strayer official) — not B.A.Sc. |
| Employment framing | Career Development · Full-time — **no Freelance** |

## Remove / avoid
- Unverified student activities (e.g. IT Student Ambassador, Data Analytics Club) unless confirmed in iCampus
- Unit-volume metrics (e.g. 3,500+ units/day)
- Leading with Copilot, Cursor, Playwright, or "I built my website"
- GPA 3.5 or unrounded 3.435 on public-facing copy
- Dead resume PDF URLs — site uses resume on request via email/portfolio

## TrueBlue / logistics bullets
- Floor ops, reconciliation, audit workflows, WMS/ERP, inventory accuracy
- SQL and data management as analyst tools — not developer identity

## After public site edits
- User pushes when ready; site deploys from `main` via GitHub Pages
- Remind to sync LinkedIn if headline, GPA, or experience bullets changed
